<hl>
<seg id=1> China Has Become A Large Manufacturer And Exporter Of Eiderdown </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Beijing, September 1 (Xinhua News Agenc) Eiderdown and its product industries have grown fast in China for the past ten years.  They have become an important part of China's light industry.  The amount and value of China's annual eiderdown export makes up half of the world eiderdown trade.  Chinese eiderdown enjoys a great reputation in the international market. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> China's eiderdown and its product industries took off in the mid-1980s.  They greatly improved the quality and quantity of their products by taking full advantage of China's huge labor and resource market and introducing advanced foreign technologies and equipments. </seg>
<seg id=4> According to a rough statistic figure, China has three thousand enterprises in eiderdown and its product industries, among which six hundred are large enterprises.  There are three hundred thousand people working in these industries.  The total manufacturing capacity of these industries can reach 50 million eiderdown products per year, with an annual industrial output 8 billion yuan. </seg>
<seg id=5> With more than ten years' efforts in expanding market, China has become a chief eiderdown manufacturer and exporter in the world.  It exports nearly thirty thousand tons of eiderdown, twenty million pieces of eiderdown products and earns 820 million US dollars annually. The export of down jackets makes up over half of the total value. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It is said that China has been making constant improvement in the quality of the eiderdown products. </seg>
<seg id=7> In the first half of this year the nation randomly examined products of 56 eiderdown enterprise.  84 percent of the enterprises, i.e. 47 of them passed all product examination. </seg>
<seg id=8> In the fierce market competition, brands like Duckie of Jiangxi Province, Yililan of Beijing, Gelanshi of Guangdong Province, and Tiange of Sichuan Province have won high reputation. </seg>
</p>
